The paper deals with compressed sensing of stochastic processes, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques (cs.SI) and the impact of measurement noise (cs.SP) on the performance of the proposed algorithms. Finally, the paper mentions the use of discrete-continuous mixture distributions (cs.MM) in the analysis of the minimum number of required measurements.
